estoration of female hormones
Without correcting hormone levels to that of a 30-35 year old, you cannot enjoy optimum health and prevent chronic
disease. Many clients with CardioMetabolic disease cannot recover without replacing testosterone, thyroid and other
hormones (BHRT is safe and efective).
Progesterone
stimulates and regulates important functions like preparing the
body for conception, maintaining pregnancy and regulating the menstrual cycle.
Testosterone
womens ovaries and adrenal glands share the responsibility for
testosterone production. Studies show that testosterone helps women maintain
muscle and bone strength, and contributes to sex drive or libido.
Estrogen
maintains the health of the reproductive organs and facilitates the
fertilization process in women. In both sexes, E2 plays a role in protecting the
heart, bones, and brain. Estrogen levels drop dramatically after women undergo
menopause.
FSH
regulates the development, growth, pubertal maturation, and reproductive
processes of the female body.
Thyroid
blood tests for thyroid are often wrong. It is impossible to lose weight
and have energy if levels are not optimal (Thyroex is a better diagnostic test
than blood tests for thyroid function).
Cortisol
is released in response to stress, acting to restore homeostasis.
However, prolonged cortisol secretion results in signicant negative physiological
changes.
Insulin
is a hormone, produced by the pancreas, which is central to regulating
carbohydrate, protein, and fat metabolism in the body. Without it, the body cannot
control or properly use glucose (sugar) one of its main energy supplying fuels.
VitD3
plays a role in controlling the immune system increasing neuromuscular
function, improving mood, and protecting the brain and heart against toxic
chemicals. It is also important for sleep, sugar control and bone health.
IgF
is
measured to help diagnose the cause of growth abnormalities, evaluate
pituitary function, and monitor treatment of Growth Hormone deciencies and
excesses. Many consider this an important hormone to combat the efects of aging.
DHEA
regulates the reproductive hormones estrogen and testosterone, and is
important for bone health. DHEA is a neuroactive steroid and regulates mood.
LH
levels are useful in the investigation of menstrual irregularities, infertility and to
aid in the diagnosis of pituitary disorders or diseases involving the ovaries or testes.
